134static std::optional<Color> parseColor(RefPtr<JSON::Object>&& colorObject)
135{
136 if (!colorObject)
137 return std::nullopt;
138
139 auto r = colorObject->getInteger(Protocol::DOM::RGBAColor::rKey);
140 auto g = colorObject->getInteger(Protocol::DOM::RGBAColor::gKey);
141 auto b = colorObject->getInteger(Protocol::DOM::RGBAColor::bKey);
142 if (!r || !g || !b)
143 return std::nullopt;
144
145 auto a = colorObject->getDouble(Protocol::DOM::RGBAColor::aKey);
146 if (!a)
147 return { makeFromComponentsClamping<SRGBA<uint8_t>>(*r, *g, *b) };
148 return { makeFromComponentsClampingExceptAlpha<SRGBA<uint8_t>>(*r, *g, *b, convertFloatAlphaTo<uint8_t>(*a)) };
149}
150
151static Color parseConfigColor(const String& fieldName, JSON::Object& configObject)
152{
153 return parseColor(configObject.getObject(fieldName)).value_or(Color::transparentBlack);
154}
155
156static bool parseQuad(Ref<JSON::Array>&& quadArray, FloatQuad* quad)
157{
158 const size_t coordinatesInQuad = 8;
159 double coordinates[coordinatesInQuad];
160 if (quadArray->length() != coordinatesInQuad)
161 return false;
162 for (size_t i = 0; i < coordinatesInQuad; ++i) {
163 auto coordinate = quadArray->get(i)->asDouble();
164 if (!coordinate)
165 return false;
166 coordinates[i] = *coordinate;
167 }
168 quad->setP1(FloatPoint(coordinates[0], coordinates[1]));
169 quad->setP2(FloatPoint(coordinates[2], coordinates[3]));
170 quad->setP3(FloatPoint(coordinates[4], coordinates[5]));
171 quad->setP4(FloatPoint(coordinates[6], coordinates[7]));
172
173 return true;
174}

176class RevalidateStyleAttributeTask {
177 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
178public:
179 RevalidateStyleAttributeTask(InspectorDOMAgent*);
180 void scheduleFor(Element*);
181 void reset() { m_timer.stop(); }
182 void timerFired();
183
184private:
185 InspectorDOMAgent* m_domAgent;
186 Timer m_timer;
187 HashSet<RefPtr<Element>> m_elements;
188};
189
190RevalidateStyleAttributeTask::RevalidateStyleAttributeTask(InspectorDOMAgent* domAgent)
191 : m_domAgent(domAgent)
192 , m_timer(*this, &RevalidateStyleAttributeTask::timerFired)
193{
194}
195
196void RevalidateStyleAttributeTask::scheduleFor(Element* element)
197{
198 m_elements.add(element);
199 if (!m_timer.isActive())
200 m_timer.startOneShot(0_s);
201}
202
203void RevalidateStyleAttributeTask::timerFired()
204{
205 // The timer is stopped on m_domAgent destruction, so this method will never be called after m_domAgent has been destroyed.
206 Vector<Element*> elements;
207 for (auto& element : m_elements)
208 elements.append(element.get());
209 m_domAgent->styleAttributeInvalidated(elements);
210
211 m_elements.clear();
212}

229class EventFiredCallback final : public EventListener {
230public:
231 static Ref<EventFiredCallback> create(InspectorDOMAgent& domAgent)
232 {
233 return adoptRef(*new EventFiredCallback(domAgent));
234 }
235
236 bool operator==(const EventListener& other) const final
237 {
238 return this == &other;
239 }
240
241 void handleEvent(ScriptExecutionContext&, Event& event) final
242 {
243 if (!is<Node>(event.target()) || m_domAgent.m_dispatchedEvents.contains(&event))
244 return;
245
246 auto* node = downcast<Node>(event.target());
247 auto nodeId = m_domAgent.pushNodePathToFrontend(node);
248 if (!nodeId)
249 return;
250
251 m_domAgent.m_dispatchedEvents.add(&event);
252
253 RefPtr<JSON::Object> data = JSON::Object::create();
254
255#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
256 if (event.type() == eventNames().webkitfullscreenchangeEvent)
257 data->setBoolean("enabled"_s, !!node->document().fullscreenManager().fullscreenElement());
258#endif // ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
259
260 auto timestamp = m_domAgent.m_environment.executionStopwatch().elapsedTime().seconds();
261 m_domAgent.m_frontendDispatcher->didFireEvent(nodeId, event.type(), timestamp, data->size() ? WTFMove(data) : nullptr);
262 }
263
264private:
265 EventFiredCallback(InspectorDOMAgent& domAgent)
266 : EventListener(EventListener::CPPEventListenerType)
267 , m_domAgent(domAgent)
268 {
269 }
270
271 InspectorDOMAgent& m_domAgent;
272};

300void InspectorDOMAgent::didCreateFrontendAndBackend(Inspector::FrontendRouter*, Inspector::BackendDispatcher*)
301{
302 m_history = makeUnique<InspectorHistory>();
303 m_domEditor = makeUnique<DOMEditor>(*m_history);
304
305 m_instrumentingAgents.setPersistentDOMAgent(this);
306 m_document = m_inspectedPage.mainFrame().document();
307
308#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
309 if (m_document)
310 addEventListenersToNode(*m_document);
311
312 for (auto* mediaElement : HTMLMediaElement::allMediaElements())
313 addEventListenersToNode(*mediaElement);
314#endif
315}
316
317void InspectorDOMAgent::willDestroyFrontendAndBackend(Inspector::DisconnectReason)
318{
319 m_history.reset();
320 m_domEditor.reset();
321 m_nodeToFocus = nullptr;
322 m_mousedOverNode = nullptr;
323 m_inspectedNode = nullptr;
324
325 Protocol::ErrorString ignored;
326 setSearchingForNode(ignored, false, nullptr, false);
327 hideHighlight();
328
329 m_overlay->clearAllGridOverlays();
330
331 m_instrumentingAgents.setPersistentDOMAgent(nullptr);
332 m_documentRequested = false;
333 reset();
334}
335
336Vector<Document*> InspectorDOMAgent::documents()
337{
338 Vector<Document*> result;
339 for (Frame* frame = m_document->frame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext()) {
340 Document* document = frame->document();
341 if (!document)
342 continue;
343 result.append(document);
344 }
345 return result;
346}
347
348void InspectorDOMAgent::reset()
349{
350 if (m_history)
351 m_history->reset();
352 m_searchResults.clear();
353 discardBindings();
354 if (m_revalidateStyleAttrTask)
355 m_revalidateStyleAttrTask->reset();
356 m_document = nullptr;
357
358 m_destroyedDetachedNodeIdentifiers.clear();
359 m_destroyedAttachedNodeIdentifiers.clear();
360 if (m_destroyedNodesTimer.isActive())
361 m_destroyedNodesTimer.stop();
362}
363
364void InspectorDOMAgent::setDocument(Document* document)
365{
366 if (document == m_document.get())
367 return;
368
369 reset();
370
371 m_document = document;
372
373 if (!m_documentRequested)
374 return;
375
376 // Immediately communicate null document or document that has finished loading.
377 if (!document || !document->parsing())
378 m_frontendDispatcher->documentUpdated();
379}

381Protocol::DOM::NodeId InspectorDOMAgent::bind(Node& node)
382{
383 return m_nodeToId.ensure(node, [&] {
384 auto id = m_lastNodeId++;
385 m_idToNode.set(id, makeWeakPtr(node));
386 return id;
387 }).iterator->value;
388}
389
390void InspectorDOMAgent::unbind(Node& node)
391{
392 auto id = m_nodeToId.take(node);
393 if (!id)
394 return;
395
396 m_idToNode.remove(id);
397
398 if (node.isFrameOwnerElement()) {
399 const HTMLFrameOwnerElement* frameOwner = static_cast<const HTMLFrameOwnerElement*>(&node);
400 if (Document* contentDocument = frameOwner->contentDocument())
401 unbind(*contentDocument);
402 }
403
404 if (is<Element>(node)) {
405 Element& element = downcast<Element>(node);
406 if (ShadowRoot* root = element.shadowRoot())
407 unbind(*root);
408 if (PseudoElement* beforeElement = element.beforePseudoElement())
409 unbind(*beforeElement);
410 if (PseudoElement* afterElement = element.afterPseudoElement())
411 unbind(*afterElement);
412 }
413
414 if (auto* cssAgent = m_instrumentingAgents.enabledCSSAgent())
415 cssAgent->didRemoveDOMNode(node, id);
416
417 if (m_childrenRequested.remove(id)) {
418 // FIXME: Would be better to do this iteratively rather than recursively.
419 for (Node* child = innerFirstChild(&node); child; child = innerNextSibling(child))
420 unbind(*child);
421 }
422}

424Node* InspectorDOMAgent::assertNode(Protocol::ErrorString& errorString, Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId)
425{
426 Node* node = nodeForId(nodeId);
427 if (!node) {
428 errorString = "Missing node for given nodeId"_s;
429 return nullptr;
430 }
431 return node;

458Node* InspectorDOMAgent::assertEditableNode(Protocol::ErrorString& errorString, Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId)
459{
460 Node* node = assertNode(errorString, nodeId);
461 if (!node)
462 return nullptr;
463 if (node->isInUserAgentShadowTree() && !m_allowEditingUserAgentShadowTrees) {
464 errorString = "Node for given nodeId is in a shadow tree"_s;
465 return nullptr;
466 }
467 if (node->isPseudoElement()) {
468 errorString = "Node for given nodeId is a pseudo-element"_s;
469 return nullptr;
470 }
471 return node;
472}

485
486Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Ref<Protocol::DOM::Node>> InspectorDOMAgent::getDocument()
487{
488 m_documentRequested = true;
489
490 if (!m_document)
491 return makeUnexpected("Internal error: missing document"_s);
492
493 // Reset backend state.
494 RefPtr<Document> document = m_document;
495 reset();
496 m_document = document;
497
498 auto root = buildObjectForNode(m_document.get(), 2);
499
500 if (m_nodeToFocus)
501 focusNode();
502
503 return root;
504}
505
506void InspectorDOMAgent::pushChildNodesToFrontend(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, int depth)
507{
508 Node* node = nodeForId(nodeId);
509 if (!node || (node->nodeType() != Node::ELEMENT_NODE && node->nodeType() != Node::DOCUMENT_NODE && node->nodeType() != Node::DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE))
510 return;
511
512 if (m_childrenRequested.contains(nodeId)) {
513 if (depth <= 1)
514 return;
515
516 depth--;
517
518 for (node = innerFirstChild(node); node; node = innerNextSibling(node)) {
519 auto childNodeId = boundNodeId(node);
520 ASSERT(childNodeId);
521 pushChildNodesToFrontend(childNodeId, depth);
522 }
523
524 return;
525 }
526
527 auto children = buildArrayForContainerChildren(node, depth);
528 m_frontendDispatcher->setChildNodes(nodeId, WTFMove(children));
529}

531void InspectorDOMAgent::discardBindings()

533 m_nodeToId.clear();

536 m_eventListenerEntries.clear();
537 m_childrenRequested.clear();

540Protocol::DOM::NodeId InspectorDOMAgent::pushNodeToFrontend(Node* nodeToPush)
541{
542 if (!nodeToPush)
543 return 0;
544
545 // FIXME: <https://webkit.org/b/213499> Web Inspector: allow DOM nodes to be instrumented at any point, regardless of whether the main document has also been instrumented
546
547 Protocol::ErrorString ignored;
548 return pushNodeToFrontend(ignored, boundNodeId(&nodeToPush->document()), nodeToPush);
549}
550
551Protocol::DOM::NodeId InspectorDOMAgent::pushNodeToFrontend(Protocol::ErrorString& errorString, Protocol::DOM::NodeId documentNodeId, Node* nodeToPush)
552{
553 Document* document = assertDocument(errorString, documentNodeId);
554 if (!document)
555 return 0;
556 if (&nodeToPush->document() != document) {
557 errorString = "nodeToPush is not part of the document with given documentNodeId"_s;
558 return 0;
559 }
560
561 return pushNodePathToFrontend(errorString, nodeToPush);
562}
563
564Node* InspectorDOMAgent::nodeForId(Protocol::DOM::NodeId id)
565{
566 if (!m_idToNode.isValidKey(id))
567 return nullptr;
568
569 return m_idToNode.get(id).get();
570}

572Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorDOMAgent::requestChildNodes(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, std::optional<int>&& depth)
573{
574 int sanitizedDepth;
575
576 if (!depth)
577 sanitizedDepth = 1;
578 else if (*depth == -1)
579 sanitizedDepth = INT_MAX;
580 else if (*depth > 0)
581 sanitizedDepth = *depth;
582 else
583 return makeUnexpected("Unexpected value below -1 for given depth"_s);
584
585 pushChildNodesToFrontend(nodeId, sanitizedDepth);
586
587 return { };
588}

590Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Protocol::DOM::NodeId> InspectorDOMAgent::querySelector(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, const String& selector)
591{
592 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
593
594 Node* node = assertNode(errorString, nodeId);
595 if (!node)
596 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
597 if (!is<ContainerNode>(*node))
598 return makeUnexpected("Node for given nodeId is not a container node"_s);
599
600 auto queryResult = downcast<ContainerNode>(*node).querySelector(selector);
601 if (queryResult.hasException())
602 return makeUnexpected(InspectorDOMAgent::toErrorString(queryResult.releaseException()));
603
604 auto resultNodeId = pushNodePathToFrontend(errorString, queryResult.releaseReturnValue());
605 if (!resultNodeId)
606 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
607
608 return resultNodeId;
609}
610
611Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>>> InspectorDOMAgent::querySelectorAll(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, const String& selector)
612{
613 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
614
615 Node* node = assertNode(errorString, nodeId);
616 if (!node)
617 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
618 if (!is<ContainerNode>(*node))
619 return makeUnexpected("Node for given nodeId is not a container node"_s);
620
621 auto queryResult = downcast<ContainerNode>(*node).querySelectorAll(selector);
622 if (queryResult.hasException())
623 return makeUnexpected(InspectorDOMAgent::toErrorString(queryResult.releaseException()));
624
625 auto nodes = queryResult.releaseReturnValue();
626
627 auto nodeIds = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>::create();
628 for (unsigned i = 0; i < nodes->length(); ++i)
629 nodeIds->addItem(pushNodePathToFrontend(nodes->item(i)));
630 return nodeIds;
631}
632
633Protocol::DOM::NodeId InspectorDOMAgent::pushNodePathToFrontend(Node* nodeToPush)
634{
635 Protocol::ErrorString ignored;
636 return pushNodePathToFrontend(ignored, nodeToPush);
637}
638
639Protocol::DOM::NodeId InspectorDOMAgent::pushNodePathToFrontend(Protocol::ErrorString errorString, Node* nodeToPush)
640{
641 ASSERT(nodeToPush); // Invalid input
642
643 if (!m_document) {
644 errorString = "Missing document"_s;
645 return 0;
646 }
647
648 // FIXME: <https://webkit.org/b/213499> Web Inspector: allow DOM nodes to be instrumented at any point, regardless of whether the main document has also been instrumented
649 if (!m_nodeToId.contains(*m_document)) {
650 errorString = "Document must have been requested"_s;
651 return 0;
652 }
653
654 // Return id in case the node is known.
655 if (auto result = boundNodeId(nodeToPush))
656 return result;
657
658 Node* node = nodeToPush;
659 Vector<Node*> path;
660
661 while (true) {
662 Node* parent = innerParentNode(node);
663 if (!parent) {
664 // Node being pushed is detached -> push subtree root.
665 auto children = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::Node>::create();
666 children->addItem(buildObjectForNode(node, 0));
667 m_frontendDispatcher->setChildNodes(0, WTFMove(children));
668 break;
669 } else {
670 path.append(parent);
671 if (boundNodeId(parent))
672 break;
673 node = parent;
674 }
675 }
676
677 for (int i = path.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
678 auto nodeId = boundNodeId(path.at(i));
679 ASSERT(nodeId);
680 pushChildNodesToFrontend(nodeId);
681 }
682 return boundNodeId(nodeToPush);
683}
684
685Protocol::DOM::NodeId InspectorDOMAgent::boundNodeId(const Node* node)
686{
687 if (!node)
688 return 0;
689
690 return m_nodeToId.get(*node);
691}

693Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorDOMAgent::setAttributeValue(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, const String& name, const String& value)
694{
695 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
696
697 Element* element = assertEditableElement(errorString, nodeId);
698 if (!element)
699 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
700
701 if (!m_domEditor->setAttribute(*element, name, value, errorString))
702 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
703
704 return { };
705}
706
707Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorDOMAgent::setAttributesAsText(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, const String& text, const String& name)
708{
709 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
710
711 Element* element = assertEditableElement(errorString, nodeId);
712 if (!element)
713 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
714
715 auto parsedElement = createHTMLElement(element->document(), spanTag);
716 auto result = parsedElement.get().setInnerHTML("<span " + text + "></span>");
717 if (result.hasException())
718 return makeUnexpected(InspectorDOMAgent::toErrorString(result.releaseException()));
719
720 Node* child = parsedElement->firstChild();
721 if (!child)
722 return makeUnexpected("Could not parse given text"_s);
723
724 Element* childElement = downcast<Element>(child);
725 if (!childElement->hasAttributes() && !!name) {
726 if (!m_domEditor->removeAttribute(*element, name, errorString))
727 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
728 return { };
729 }
730
731 bool foundOriginalAttribute = false;
732 for (const Attribute& attribute : childElement->attributesIterator()) {
733 // Add attribute pair
734 foundOriginalAttribute = foundOriginalAttribute || attribute.name().toString() == name;
735 if (!m_domEditor->setAttribute(*element, attribute.name().toString(), attribute.value(), errorString))
736 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
737 }
738
739 if (!foundOriginalAttribute && !name.stripWhiteSpace().isEmpty()) {
740 if (!m_domEditor->removeAttribute(*element, name, errorString))
741 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
742 }
743
744 return { };

778
779Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Protocol::DOM::NodeId> InspectorDOMAgent::setNodeName(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, const String& tagName)
780{
781 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
782
783 auto oldNode = assertElement(errorString, nodeId);
784 if (!oldNode)
785 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
786
787 auto createElementResult = oldNode->document().createElementForBindings(tagName);
788 if (createElementResult.hasException())
789 return makeUnexpected(InspectorDOMAgent::toErrorString(createElementResult.releaseException()));
790
791 auto newElement = createElementResult.releaseReturnValue();
792
793 // Copy over the original node's attributes.
794 newElement->cloneAttributesFromElement(*oldNode);
795
796 // Copy over the original node's children.
797 RefPtr<Node> child;
798 while ((child = oldNode->firstChild())) {
799 if (!m_domEditor->insertBefore(newElement, *child, 0, errorString))
800 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
801 }
802
803 // Replace the old node with the new node
804 RefPtr<ContainerNode> parent = oldNode->parentNode();
805 if (!m_domEditor->insertBefore(*parent, newElement.copyRef(), oldNode->nextSibling(), errorString))
806 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
807 if (!m_domEditor->removeChild(*parent, *oldNode, errorString))
808 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
809
810 auto resultNodeId = pushNodePathToFrontend(errorString, newElement.ptr());
811 if (m_childrenRequested.contains(nodeId))
812 pushChildNodesToFrontend(resultNodeId);
813
814 return resultNodeId;
815}

820
821 Node* node = assertNode(errorString, nodeId);

827
828Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorDOMAgent::setOuterHTML(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId, const String& outerHTML)
829{
830 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
831
832 if (!nodeId) {
833 DOMPatchSupport { *m_domEditor, *m_document }.patchDocument(outerHTML);
834 return { };
835 }
836
837 Node* node = assertEditableNode(errorString, nodeId);
838 if (!node)
839 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
840
841 Document& document = node->document();
842 if (!document.isHTMLDocument() && !document.isXMLDocument())
843 return makeUnexpected("Document of node for given nodeId is not HTML/XML"_s);
844
845 Node* newNode = nullptr;
846 if (!m_domEditor->setOuterHTML(*node, outerHTML, newNode, errorString))
847 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
848
849 if (!newNode) {
850 // The only child node has been deleted.
851 return { };
852 }
853
854 auto newId = pushNodePathToFrontend(errorString, newNode);
855
856 bool childrenRequested = m_childrenRequested.contains(nodeId);
857 if (childrenRequested)
858 pushChildNodesToFrontend(newId);
859
860 return { };
861}

920Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::EventListener>>> InspectorDOMAgent::getEventListenersForNode(Protocol::DOM::NodeId nodeId)
921{
922 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
923
924 auto* node = assertNode(errorString, nodeId);
925 if (!node)
926 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
927
928 Vector<RefPtr<EventTarget>> ancestors;
929 ancestors.append(node);
930 for (auto* ancestor = node->parentOrShadowHostNode(); ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->parentOrShadowHostNode())
931 ancestors.append(ancestor);
932 if (auto* window = node->document().domWindow())
933 ancestors.append(window);
934
935 struct EventListenerInfo {
936 RefPtr<EventTarget> eventTarget;
937 const AtomString eventType;
938 const EventListenerVector eventListeners;
939 };
940
941 Vector<EventListenerInfo> eventInformation;
942 for (size_t i = ancestors.size(); i; --i) {
943 auto& ancestor = ancestors[i - 1];
944 for (auto& eventType : ancestor->eventTypes()) {
945 EventListenerVector filteredListeners;
946 for (auto& listener : ancestor->eventListeners(eventType)) {
947 if (listener->callback().type() == EventListener::JSEventListenerType)
948 filteredListeners.append(listener);
949 }
950 if (!filteredListeners.isEmpty())
951 eventInformation.append({ ancestor, eventType, WTFMove(filteredListeners) });
952 }
953 }
954
955 auto listeners = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::EventListener>::create();
956
957 auto addListener = [&] (RegisteredEventListener& listener, const EventListenerInfo& info) {
958 Protocol::DOM::EventListenerId identifier = 0;
959 bool disabled = false;
960 RefPtr<JSC::Breakpoint> breakpoint;
961
962 for (auto& inspectorEventListener : m_eventListenerEntries.values()) {
963 if (inspectorEventListener.matches(*info.eventTarget, info.eventType, listener.callback(), listener.useCapture())) {
964 identifier = inspectorEventListener.identifier;
965 disabled = inspectorEventListener.disabled;
966 breakpoint = inspectorEventListener.breakpoint;
967 break;
968 }
969 }
970
971 if (!identifier) {
972 InspectorEventListener inspectorEventListener(m_lastEventListenerId++, *info.eventTarget, info.eventType, listener.callback(), listener.useCapture());
973
974 identifier = inspectorEventListener.identifier;
975 disabled = inspectorEventListener.disabled;
976 breakpoint = inspectorEventListener.breakpoint;
977
978 m_eventListenerEntries.add(identifier, inspectorEventListener);
979 }
980
981 listeners->addItem(buildObjectForEventListener(listener, identifier, *info.eventTarget, info.eventType, disabled, breakpoint));
982 };
983
984 // Get Capturing Listeners (in this order)
985 size_t eventInformationLength = eventInformation.size();
986 for (auto& info : eventInformation) {
987 for (auto& listener : info.eventListeners) {
988 if (listener->useCapture())
989 addListener(*listener, info);
990 }
991 }
992
993 // Get Bubbling Listeners (reverse order)
994 for (size_t i = eventInformationLength; i; --i) {
995 const EventListenerInfo& info = eventInformation[i - 1];
996 for (auto& listener : info.eventListeners) {
997 if (!listener->useCapture())
998 addListener(*listener, info);
999 }
1000 }
1001
1002 if (m_inspectedNode == node)
1003 m_suppressEventListenerChangedEvent = false;
1004
1005 return listeners;
1006}

1062Protocol::ErrorStringOr<std::tuple<String /* searchId */, int /* resultCount */>> InspectorDOMAgent::performSearch(const String& query, RefPtr<JSON::Array>&& nodeIds, std::optional<bool>&& caseSensitive)
1063{
1064 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
1065
1066 // FIXME: Search works with node granularity - number of matches within node is not calculated.
1067 InspectorNodeFinder finder(query, caseSensitive && *caseSensitive);
1068
1069 if (nodeIds) {
1070 for (auto& nodeValue : *nodeIds) {
1071 auto nodeId = nodeValue->asInteger();
1072 if (!nodeId)
1073 return makeUnexpected("Unexpected non-integer item in given nodeIds"_s);
1074
1075 Node* node = assertNode(errorString, *nodeId);
1076 if (!node)
1077 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
1078
1079 finder.performSearch(node);
1080 }
1081 } else {
1082 // There's no need to iterate the frames tree because
1083 // the search helper will go inside the frame owner elements.
1084 finder.performSearch(m_document.get());
1085 }
1086
1087 auto searchId = IdentifiersFactory::createIdentifier();
1088
1089 auto& resultsVector = m_searchResults.add(searchId, Vector<RefPtr<Node>>()).iterator->value;
1090 for (auto& result : finder.results())
1091 resultsVector.append(result);
1092
1093 return { { searchId, resultsVector.size() } };
1094}
1095
1096Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>>> InspectorDOMAgent::getSearchResults(const String& searchId, int fromIndex, int toIndex)
1097{
1098 SearchResults::iterator it = m_searchResults.find(searchId);
1099 if (it == m_searchResults.end())
1100 return makeUnexpected("Missing search result for given searchId"_s);
1101
1102 int size = it->value.size();
1103 if (fromIndex < 0 || toIndex > size || fromIndex >= toIndex)
1104 return makeUnexpected("Invalid search result range for given fromIndex and toIndex"_s);
1105
1106 auto nodeIds = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>::create();
1107 for (int i = fromIndex; i < toIndex; ++i)
1108 nodeIds->addItem(pushNodePathToFrontend((it->value)[i].get()));
1109 return nodeIds;
1110}

1159void InspectorDOMAgent::focusNode()
1160{
1161 // FIXME: <https://webkit.org/b/213499> Web Inspector: allow DOM nodes to be instrumented at any point, regardless of whether the main document has also been instrumented
1162 if (!m_documentRequested)
1163 return;
1164
1165 ASSERT(m_nodeToFocus);
1166
1167 RefPtr<Node> node = m_nodeToFocus.get();
1168 m_nodeToFocus = nullptr;
1169
1170 Frame* frame = node->document().frame();
1171 if (!frame)
1172 return;
1173
1174 JSC::JSGlobalObject* scriptState = mainWorldExecState(frame);
1175 InjectedScript injectedScript = m_injectedScriptManager.injectedScriptFor(scriptState);
1176 if (injectedScript.hasNoValue())
1177 return;
1178
1179 injectedScript.inspectObject(nodeAsScriptValue(*scriptState, node.get()));
1180}

1293
1294Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorDOMAgent::highlightSelector(Ref<JSON::Object>&& highlightInspectorObject, const String& selectorString, const Protocol::Network::FrameId& frameId)
1295{
1296 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
1297
1298 auto highlightConfig = highlightConfigFromInspectorObject(errorString, WTFMove(highlightInspectorObject));
1299 if (!highlightConfig)
1300 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
1301
1302 RefPtr<Document> document;
1303
1304 if (!!frameId) {
1305 auto* pageAgent = m_instrumentingAgents.enabledPageAgent();
1306 if (!pageAgent)
1307 return makeUnexpected("Page domain must be enabled"_s);
1308
1309 auto* frame = pageAgent->assertFrame(errorString, frameId);
1310 if (!frame)
1311 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
1312
1313 document = frame->document();
1314 } else
1315 document = m_document;
1316
1317 if (!document)
1318 return makeUnexpected("Missing document of frame for given frameId"_s);
1319
1320 CSSParser parser(*document);
1321 auto selectorList = parser.parseSelector(selectorString);
1322 if (!selectorList)
1323 return { };
1324
1325 SelectorChecker selectorChecker(*document);
1326
1327 Vector<Ref<Node>> nodeList;
1328 HashSet<Ref<Node>> seenNodes;
1329
1330 for (auto& descendant : composedTreeDescendants(*document)) {
1331 if (!is<Element>(descendant))
1332 continue;
1333
1334 auto& descendantElement = downcast<Element>(descendant);
1335
1336 auto isInUserAgentShadowTree = descendantElement.isInUserAgentShadowTree();
1337 auto pseudoId = descendantElement.pseudoId();
1338 auto& pseudo = descendantElement.pseudo();
1339
1340 for (const auto* selector = selectorList->first(); selector; selector = CSSSelectorList::next(selector)) {
1341 if (isInUserAgentShadowTree && (selector->match() != CSSSelector::PseudoElement || selector->value() != pseudo))
1342 continue;
1343
1344 SelectorChecker::CheckingContext context(SelectorChecker::Mode::ResolvingStyle);
1345 context.pseudoId = pseudoId;
1346
1347 if (selectorChecker.match(*selector, descendantElement, context)) {
1348 if (seenNodes.add(descendantElement))
1349 nodeList.append(descendantElement);
1350 }
1351
1352 if (context.pseudoIDSet) {
1353 auto pseudoIDs = PseudoIdSet::fromMask(context.pseudoIDSet.data());
1354
1355 if (pseudoIDs.has(PseudoId::Before)) {
1356 pseudoIDs.remove(PseudoId::Before);
1357 if (auto* beforePseudoElement = descendantElement.beforePseudoElement()) {
1358 if (seenNodes.add(*beforePseudoElement))
1359 nodeList.append(*beforePseudoElement);
1360 }
1361 }
1362
1363 if (pseudoIDs.has(PseudoId::After)) {
1364 pseudoIDs.remove(PseudoId::After);
1365 if (auto* afterPseudoElement = descendantElement.afterPseudoElement()) {
1366 if (seenNodes.add(*afterPseudoElement))
1367 nodeList.append(*afterPseudoElement);
1368 }
1369 }
1370
1371 if (pseudoIDs) {
1372 if (seenNodes.add(descendantElement))
1373 nodeList.append(descendantElement);
1374 }
1375 }
1376 }
1377 }
1378
1379 m_overlay->highlightNodeList(StaticNodeList::create(WTFMove(nodeList)), *highlightConfig);
1380
1381 return { };
1382}

1387
1388 Node* node = nullptr;

1396

1408
1409Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorDOMAgent::highlightNodeList(Ref<JSON::Array>&& nodeIds, Ref<JSON::Object>&& highlightInspectorObject)
1410{
1411 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
1412
1413 Vector<Ref<Node>> nodes;
1414 for (auto& nodeIdValue : nodeIds.get()) {
1415 auto nodeId = nodeIdValue->asInteger();
1416 if (!nodeId)
1417 return makeUnexpected("Unexpected non-integer item in given nodeIds"_s);
1418
1419 // In the case that a node is removed in the time between when highlightNodeList is invoked
1420 // by the frontend and it is executed by the backend, we should still attempt to highlight
1421 // as many nodes as possible. As such, we should ignore any errors generated when attempting
1422 // to get a Node from a given nodeId.
1423 Protocol::ErrorString ignored;
1424 Node* node = assertNode(ignored, *nodeId);
1425 if (!node)
1426 continue;
1427
1428 nodes.append(*node);
1429 }
1430

1671 return Protocol::DOM::ShadowRootType::Closed;

1680static Protocol::DOM::CustomElementState customElementState(const Element& element)
1681{
1682 if (element.isDefinedCustomElement())
1683 return Protocol::DOM::CustomElementState::Custom;
1684 if (element.isFailedCustomElement())
1685 return Protocol::DOM::CustomElementState::Failed;
1686 if (element.isUndefinedCustomElement() || element.isCustomElementUpgradeCandidate())
1687 return Protocol::DOM::CustomElementState::Waiting;
1688 return Protocol::DOM::CustomElementState::Builtin;
1689}
1690
1691static String computeContentSecurityPolicySHA256Hash(const Element& element)
1692{
1693 // FIXME: Compute the digest with respect to the raw bytes received from the page.
1694 // See <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=155184>.
1695 TextEncoding documentEncoding = element.document().textEncoding();
1696 const TextEncoding& encodingToUse = documentEncoding.isValid() ? documentEncoding : UTF8Encoding();
1697 auto content = encodingToUse.encode(TextNodeTraversal::contentsAsString(element), UnencodableHandling::Entities);
1698 auto cryptoDigest = PAL::CryptoDigest::create(PAL::CryptoDigest::Algorithm::SHA_256);
1699 cryptoDigest->addBytes(content.data(), content.size());
1700 auto digest = cryptoDigest->computeHash();
1701 return makeString("sha256-", base64Encoded(digest.data(), digest.size()));
1702}
1703
1704Ref<Protocol::DOM::Node> InspectorDOMAgent::buildObjectForNode(Node* node, int depth)
1705{
1706 auto id = bind(*node);
1707 String nodeName;
1708 String localName;
1709 String nodeValue;
1710
1711 switch (node->nodeType()) {
1712 case Node::PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE:
1713 nodeName = node->nodeName();
1714 localName = node->localName();
1715 FALLTHROUGH;
1716 case Node::TEXT_NODE:
1717 case Node::COMMENT_NODE:
1718 case Node::CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
1719 nodeValue = node->nodeValue();
1720 if (nodeValue.length() > maxTextSize) {
1721 nodeValue = nodeValue.left(maxTextSize);
1722 nodeValue.append(ellipsisUChar);
1723 }
1724 break;
1725 case Node::ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
1726 localName = node->localName();
1727 break;
1728 case Node::DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE:
1729 case Node::DOCUMENT_NODE:
1730 case Node::ELEMENT_NODE:
1731 default:
1732 nodeName = node->nodeName();
1733 localName = node->localName();
1734 break;
1735 }
1736
1737 auto value = Protocol::DOM::Node::create()
1738 .setNodeId(id)
1739 .setNodeType(static_cast<int>(node->nodeType()))
1740 .setNodeName(nodeName)
1741 .setLocalName(localName)
1742 .setNodeValue(nodeValue)
1743 .release();
1744
1745 if (node->isContainerNode()) {
1746 int nodeCount = innerChildNodeCount(node);
1747 value->setChildNodeCount(nodeCount);
1748 auto children = buildArrayForContainerChildren(node, depth);
1749 if (children->length() > 0)
1750 value->setChildren(WTFMove(children));
1751 }
1752
1753 if (auto layoutContextType = InspectorCSSAgent::layoutContextTypeForRenderer(node->renderer()))
1754 value->setLayoutContextType(layoutContextType.value());
1755
1756 auto* pageAgent = m_instrumentingAgents.enabledPageAgent();
1757 if (pageAgent) {
1758 if (auto* frameView = node->document().view())
1759 value->setFrameId(pageAgent->frameId(&frameView->frame()));
1760 }
1761
1762 if (is<Element>(*node)) {
1763 Element& element = downcast<Element>(*node);
1764 value->setAttributes(buildArrayForElementAttributes(&element));
1765 if (is<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(element)) {
1766 if (auto* document = downcast<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(element).contentDocument())
1767 value->setContentDocument(buildObjectForNode(document, 0));
1768 }
1769
1770 if (ShadowRoot* root = element.shadowRoot()) {
1771 auto shadowRoots = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::Node>::create();
1772 shadowRoots->addItem(buildObjectForNode(root, 0));
1773 value->setShadowRoots(WTFMove(shadowRoots));
1774 }
1775
1776 if (is<HTMLTemplateElement>(element))
1777 value->setTemplateContent(buildObjectForNode(&downcast<HTMLTemplateElement>(element).content(), 0));
1778
1779 if (is<HTMLStyleElement>(element) || (is<HTMLScriptElement>(element) && !element.hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(HTMLNames::srcAttr)))
1780 value->setContentSecurityPolicyHash(computeContentSecurityPolicySHA256Hash(element));
1781
1782 auto state = customElementState(element);
1783 if (state != Protocol::DOM::CustomElementState::Builtin)
1784 value->setCustomElementState(state);
1785
1786 if (element.pseudoId() != PseudoId::None) {
1787 Protocol::DOM::PseudoType pseudoType;
1788 if (pseudoElementType(element.pseudoId(), &pseudoType))
1789 value->setPseudoType(pseudoType);
1790 } else {
1791 if (auto pseudoElements = buildArrayForPseudoElements(element))
1792 value->setPseudoElements(pseudoElements.releaseNonNull());
1793 }
1794 } else if (is<Document>(*node)) {
1795 Document& document = downcast<Document>(*node);
1796 if (pageAgent)
1797 value->setFrameId(pageAgent->frameId(document.frame()));
1798 value->setDocumentURL(documentURLString(&document));
1799 value->setBaseURL(documentBaseURLString(&document));
1800 value->setXmlVersion(document.xmlVersion());
1801 } else if (is<DocumentType>(*node)) {
1802 DocumentType& docType = downcast<DocumentType>(*node);
1803 value->setPublicId(docType.publicId());
1804 value->setSystemId(docType.systemId());
1805 } else if (is<Attr>(*node)) {
1806 Attr& attribute = downcast<Attr>(*node);
1807 value->setName(attribute.name());
1808 value->setValue(attribute.value());
1809 } else if (is<ShadowRoot>(*node)) {
1810 ShadowRoot& shadowRoot = downcast<ShadowRoot>(*node);
1811 value->setShadowRootType(shadowRootType(shadowRoot.mode()));
1812 }
1813
1814 return value;
1815}
1816
1817Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<String>> InspectorDOMAgent::buildArrayForElementAttributes(Element* element)
1818{
1819 auto attributesValue = JSON::ArrayOf<String>::create();
1820 // Go through all attributes and serialize them.
1821 if (!element->hasAttributes())
1822 return attributesValue;
1823 for (const Attribute& attribute : element->attributesIterator()) {
1824 // Add attribute pair
1825 attributesValue->addItem(attribute.name().toString());
1826 attributesValue->addItem(attribute.value());
1827 }
1828 return attributesValue;
1829}
1830
1831Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::Node>> InspectorDOMAgent::buildArrayForContainerChildren(Node* container, int depth)
1832{
1833 auto children = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::Node>::create();
1834 if (depth == 0) {
1835 // Special-case the only text child - pretend that container's children have been requested.
1836 Node* firstChild = container->firstChild();
1837 if (firstChild && firstChild->nodeType() == Node::TEXT_NODE && !firstChild->nextSibling()) {
1838 children->addItem(buildObjectForNode(firstChild, 0));
1839 m_childrenRequested.add(bind(*container));
1840 }
1841 return children;
1842 }
1843
1844 Node* child = innerFirstChild(container);
1845 depth--;
1846 m_childrenRequested.add(bind(*container));
1847
1848 while (child) {
1849 children->addItem(buildObjectForNode(child, depth));
1850 child = innerNextSibling(child);
1851 }
1852 return children;
1853}
1854
1855RefPtr<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::Node>> InspectorDOMAgent::buildArrayForPseudoElements(const Element& element)
1856{
1857 PseudoElement* beforeElement = element.beforePseudoElement();
1858 PseudoElement* afterElement = element.afterPseudoElement();
1859 if (!beforeElement && !afterElement)
1860 return nullptr;
1861
1862 auto pseudoElements = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::Node>::create();
1863 if (beforeElement)
1864 pseudoElements->addItem(buildObjectForNode(beforeElement, 0));
1865 if (afterElement)
1866 pseudoElements->addItem(buildObjectForNode(afterElement, 0));
1867 return pseudoElements;
1868}
1869
1870Ref<Protocol::DOM::EventListener> InspectorDOMAgent::buildObjectForEventListener(const RegisteredEventListener& registeredEventListener, Protocol::DOM::EventListenerId identifier, EventTarget& eventTarget, const AtomString& eventType, bool disabled, const RefPtr<JSC::Breakpoint>& breakpoint)
1871{
1872 Ref<EventListener> eventListener = registeredEventListener.callback();
1873
1874 String handlerName;
1875 int lineNumber = 0;
1876 int columnNumber = 0;
1877 String scriptID;
1878 if (is<JSEventListener>(eventListener.get())) {
1879 auto& scriptListener = downcast<JSEventListener>(eventListener.get());
1880
1881 Document* document = nullptr;
1882 if (auto* scriptExecutionContext = eventTarget.scriptExecutionContext()) {
1883 if (is<Document>(scriptExecutionContext))
1884 document = downcast<Document>(scriptExecutionContext);
1885 } else if (is<Node>(eventTarget))
1886 document = &downcast<Node>(eventTarget).document();
1887
1888 JSC::JSObject* handlerObject = nullptr;
1889 JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject = nullptr;
1890
1891 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(scriptListener.isolatedWorld().vm());
1892
1893 if (document) {
1894 handlerObject = scriptListener.ensureJSFunction(*document);
1895 globalObject = WebCore::globalObject(scriptListener.isolatedWorld(), document);
1896 }
1897
1898 if (handlerObject && globalObject) {
1899 JSC::VM& vm = globalObject->vm();
1900 JSC::JSFunction* handlerFunction = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSFunction*>(vm, handlerObject);
1901
1902 if (!handlerFunction) {
1903 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1904
1905 // If the handler is not actually a function, see if it implements the EventListener interface and use that.
1906 auto handleEventValue = handlerObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "handleEvent"));
1907
1908 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1909 scope.clearException();
1910
1911 if (handleEventValue)
1912 handlerFunction = JSC::jsDynamicCast<JSC::JSFunction*>(vm, handleEventValue);
1913 }
1914
1915 if (handlerFunction && !handlerFunction->isHostOrBuiltinFunction()) {
1916 // If the listener implements the EventListener interface, use the class name instead of
1917 // "handleEvent", unless it is a plain object.
1918 if (handlerFunction != handlerObject)
1919 handlerName = JSC::JSObject::calculatedClassName(handlerObject);
1920 if (handlerName.isEmpty() || handlerName == "Object"_s)
1921 handlerName = handlerFunction->calculatedDisplayName(vm);
1922
1923 if (auto executable = handlerFunction->jsExecutable()) {
1924 lineNumber = executable->firstLine() - 1;
1925 columnNumber = executable->startColumn() - 1;
1926 scriptID = executable->sourceID() == JSC::SourceProvider::nullID ? emptyString() : String::number(executable->sourceID());
1927 }
1928 }
1929 }
1930 }
1931
1932 auto value = Protocol::DOM::EventListener::create()
1933 .setEventListenerId(identifier)
1934 .setType(eventType)
1935 .setUseCapture(registeredEventListener.useCapture())
1936 .setIsAttribute(eventListener->isAttribute())
1937 .release();
1938 if (is<Node>(eventTarget))
1939 value->setNodeId(pushNodePathToFrontend(&downcast<Node>(eventTarget)));
1940 else if (is<DOMWindow>(eventTarget))
1941 value->setOnWindow(true);
1942 if (!scriptID.isNull()) {
1943 auto location = Protocol::Debugger::Location::create()
1944 .setScriptId(scriptID)
1945 .setLineNumber(lineNumber)
1946 .release();
1947 location->setColumnNumber(columnNumber);
1948 value->setLocation(WTFMove(location));
1949 }
1950 if (!handlerName.isEmpty())
1951 value->setHandlerName(handlerName);
1952 if (registeredEventListener.isPassive())
1953 value->setPassive(true);
1954 if (registeredEventListener.isOnce())
1955 value->setOnce(true);
1956 if (disabled)
1957 value->setDisabled(disabled);
1958 if (breakpoint)
1959 value->setHasBreakpoint(breakpoint);
1960 return value;
1961}
1962
1963void InspectorDOMAgent::processAccessibilityChildren(AXCoreObject& axObject, JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>& childNodeIds)
1964{
1965 const auto& children = axObject.children();
1966 if (!children.size())
1967 return;
1968
1969 for (const auto& childObject : children) {
1970 if (Node* childNode = childObject->node())
1971 childNodeIds.addItem(pushNodePathToFrontend(childNode));
1972 else
1973 processAccessibilityChildren(*childObject, childNodeIds);
1974 }
1975}
1976
1977Ref<Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties> InspectorDOMAgent::buildObjectForAccessibilityProperties(Node& node)
1978{
1979 if (!WebCore::AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled())
1980 WebCore::AXObjectCache::enableAccessibility();
1981
1982 Node* activeDescendantNode = nullptr;
1983 bool busy = false;
1984 auto checked = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Checked::False;
1985 RefPtr<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>> childNodeIds;
1986 RefPtr<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>> controlledNodeIds;
1987 auto currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::False;
1988 bool exists = false;
1989 bool expanded = false;
1990 bool disabled = false;
1991 RefPtr<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>> flowedNodeIds;
1992 bool focused = false;
1993 bool ignored = true;
1994 bool ignoredByDefault = false;
1995 auto invalid = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Invalid::False;
1996 bool hidden = false;
1997 String label;
1998 bool liveRegionAtomic = false;
1999 RefPtr<JSON::ArrayOf<String>> liveRegionRelevant;
2000 auto liveRegionStatus = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::LiveRegionStatus::Off;
2001 Node* mouseEventNode = nullptr;
2002 RefPtr<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>> ownedNodeIds;
2003 Node* parentNode = nullptr;
2004 bool pressed = false;
2005 bool readonly = false;
2006 bool required = false;
2007 String role;
2008 bool selected = false;
2009 RefPtr<JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>> selectedChildNodeIds;
2010 bool supportsChecked = false;
2011 bool supportsExpanded = false;
2012 bool supportsLiveRegion = false;
2013 bool supportsPressed = false;
2014 bool supportsRequired = false;
2015 bool supportsFocused = false;
2016 bool isPopupButton = false;
2017 int headingLevel = 0;
2018 unsigned hierarchicalLevel = 0;
2019 unsigned level = 0;
2020
2021 if (AXObjectCache* axObjectCache = node.document().axObjectCache()) {
2022 if (AXCoreObject* axObject = axObjectCache->getOrCreate(&node)) {
2023
2024 if (AXCoreObject* activeDescendant = axObject->activeDescendant())
2025 activeDescendantNode = activeDescendant->node();
2026
2027 // An AX object is "busy" if it or any ancestor has aria-busy="true" set.
2028 AXCoreObject* current = axObject;
2029 while (!busy && current) {
2030 busy = current->isBusy();
2031 current = current->parentObject();
2032 }
2033
2034 supportsChecked = axObject->supportsChecked();
2035 if (supportsChecked) {
2036 AccessibilityButtonState checkValue = axObject->checkboxOrRadioValue(); // Element using aria-checked.
2037 if (checkValue == AccessibilityButtonState::On)
2038 checked = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Checked::True;
2039 else if (checkValue == AccessibilityButtonState::Mixed)
2040 checked = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Checked::Mixed;
2041 else if (axObject->isChecked()) // Native checkbox.
2042 checked = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Checked::True;
2043 }
2044
2045 if (!axObject->children().isEmpty()) {
2046 childNodeIds = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>::create();
2047 processAccessibilityChildren(*axObject, *childNodeIds);
2048 }
2049
2050 Vector<Element*> controlledElements;
2051 axObject->elementsFromAttribute(controlledElements, aria_controlsAttr);
2052 if (controlledElements.size()) {
2053 controlledNodeIds = JSON::ArrayOf<Protocol::DOM::NodeId>::create();
2054 for (Element* controlledElement : controlledElements) {
2055 if (auto controlledElementId = pushNodePathToFrontend(controlledElement))
2056 controlledNodeIds->addItem(controlledElementId);
2057 }
2058 }
2059
2060 switch (axObject->currentState()) {
2061 case AccessibilityCurrentState::False:
2062 currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::False;
2063 break;
2064 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Page:
2065 currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::Page;
2066 break;
2067 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Step:
2068 currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::Step;
2069 break;
2070 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Location:
2071 currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::Location;
2072 break;
2073 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Date:
2074 currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::Date;
2075 break;
2076 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Time:
2077 currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::Time;
2078 break;
2079 case AccessibilityCurrentState::True:
2080 currentState = Protocol::DOM::AccessibilityProperties::Current::True;
2081 break;
2082 }
2083
2084 disabled = !axObject->isEnabled();
2085 exists = true;
2086
2087 supportsExpanded = axObject->supportsExpanded();
2088 if (supportsExpanded)
2089 expanded = axObject->isExpanded();
2090
2091 Vector<Element*> flowedElements;
2092 axObject->elementsFromAttribute(flowedElements, aria_flowtoAttr);

2340void InspectorDOMAgent::didCommitLoad(Document* document)
2341{
2342 if (m_nodeToFocus && &m_nodeToFocus->document() == document)
2343 m_nodeToFocus = nullptr;
2344
2345 if (m_mousedOverNode && &m_mousedOverNode->document() == document)
2346 m_mousedOverNode = nullptr;
2347
2348 if (m_inspectedNode && &m_inspectedNode->document() == document)
2349 m_inspectedNode = nullptr;
2350
2351 RefPtr<Element> frameOwner = document->ownerElement();
2352 if (!frameOwner)
2353 return;
2354
2355 auto frameOwnerId = boundNodeId(frameOwner.get());
2356 if (!frameOwnerId)
2357 return;
2358
2359 // Re-add frame owner element together with its new children.
2360 auto parentId = boundNodeId(innerParentNode(frameOwner.get()));
2361 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeRemoved(parentId, frameOwnerId);
2362 unbind(*frameOwner);
2363
2364 auto value = buildObjectForNode(frameOwner.get(), 0);
2365 Node* previousSibling = innerPreviousSibling(frameOwner.get());
2366 auto prevId = boundNodeId(previousSibling);
2367 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeInserted(parentId, prevId, WTFMove(value));
2368}

2415void InspectorDOMAgent::didInsertDOMNode(Node& node)
2416{
2417 if (containsOnlyHTMLWhitespace(&node))
2418 return;
2419
2420 // We could be attaching existing subtree. Forget the bindings.
2421 unbind(node);
2422
2423 ContainerNode* parent = node.parentNode();
2424
2425 auto parentId = boundNodeId(parent);
2426 // Return if parent is not mapped yet.
2427 if (!parentId)
2428 return;
2429
2430 if (!m_childrenRequested.contains(parentId)) {
2431 // No children are mapped yet -> only notify on changes of hasChildren.
2432 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeCountUpdated(parentId, innerChildNodeCount(parent));
2433 } else {
2434 // Children have been requested -> return value of a new child.
2435 Node* prevSibling = innerPreviousSibling(&node);
2436 auto prevId = boundNodeId(prevSibling);
2437 auto value = buildObjectForNode(&node, 0);
2438 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeInserted(parentId, prevId, WTFMove(value));
2439 }
2440}

2442void InspectorDOMAgent::didRemoveDOMNode(Node& node)
2443{
2444 if (containsOnlyHTMLWhitespace(&node))
2445 return;
2446
2447 ContainerNode* parent = node.parentNode();
2448
2449 auto parentId = boundNodeId(parent);
2450 // If parent is not mapped yet -> ignore the event.
2451 if (!parentId)
2452 return;
2453
2454 // FIXME: <webkit.org/b/189687> Preserve DOM.NodeId if a node is removed and re-added
2455 if (!m_childrenRequested.contains(parentId)) {
2456 // No children are mapped yet -> only notify on changes of hasChildren.
2457 if (innerChildNodeCount(parent) == 1)
2458 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeCountUpdated(parentId, 0);
2459 } else
2460 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeRemoved(parentId, boundNodeId(&node));
2461 unbind(node);
2462}

2464void InspectorDOMAgent::willDestroyDOMNode(Node& node)
2465{
2466 if (containsOnlyHTMLWhitespace(&node))
2467 return;
2468
2469 auto nodeId = m_nodeToId.take(node);
2470 if (!nodeId)
2471 return;
2472
2473 m_idToNode.remove(nodeId);
2474 m_childrenRequested.remove(nodeId);
2475
2476 if (auto* cssAgent = m_instrumentingAgents.enabledCSSAgent())
2477 cssAgent->didRemoveDOMNode(node, nodeId);
2478
2479 // This can be called in response to GC. Due to the single-process model used in WebKit1, the
2480 // event must be dispatched from a timer to prevent the frontend from making JS allocations
2481 // while the GC is still active.
2482
2483 // FIXME: <webkit.org/b/189687> Unify m_destroyedAttachedNodeIdentifiers and m_destroyedDetachedNodeIdentifiers.
2484 if (auto parentId = boundNodeId(node.parentNode()))
2485 m_destroyedAttachedNodeIdentifiers.append({ parentId, nodeId });
2486 else
2487 m_destroyedDetachedNodeIdentifiers.append(nodeId);
2488
2489 if (!m_destroyedNodesTimer.isActive())
2490 m_destroyedNodesTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
2491}
2492
2493void InspectorDOMAgent::destroyedNodesTimerFired()
2494{
2495 for (auto& [parentId, nodeId] : std::exchange(m_destroyedAttachedNodeIdentifiers, { })) {
2496 if (!m_childrenRequested.contains(parentId)) {
2497 auto* parent = nodeForId(parentId);
2498 if (parent && innerChildNodeCount(parent) == 1)
2499 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeCountUpdated(parentId, 0);
2500 } else
2501 m_frontendDispatcher->childNodeRemoved(parentId, nodeId);
2502 }
2503
2504 for (auto nodeId : std::exchange(m_destroyedDetachedNodeIdentifiers, { }))
2505 m_frontendDispatcher->willDestroyDOMNode(nodeId);
2506}

2669void InspectorDOMAgent::willRemoveEventListener(EventTarget& target, const AtomString& eventType, EventListener& listener, bool capture)
2670{
2671 if (!is<Node>(target))
2672 return;
2673
2674 auto& node = downcast<Node>(target);
2675 if (!node.contains(m_inspectedNode.get()))
2676 return;

2679 if (!nodeId)
2680 return;
2681
2682 bool listenerExists = false;
2683 for (auto& item : node.eventListeners(eventType)) {
2684 if (item->callback() == listener && item->useCapture() == capture) {
2685 listenerExists = true;

2687 }
2688 }
2689
2690 if (!listenerExists)
2691 return;
2692
2693 m_eventListenerEntries.removeIf([&] (auto& entry) {
2694 return entry.value.matches(target, eventType, listener, capture);
2695 });
2696
2697 if (m_suppressEventListenerChangedEvent)
2698 return;

2700 m_suppressEventListenerChangedEvent = true;
2701

2737#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
2738void InspectorDOMAgent::mediaMetricsTimerFired()
2739{
2740 // FIXME: remove metrics information for any media element when it's destroyed
2741
2742 if (HTMLMediaElement::allMediaElements().isEmpty()) {
2743 if (m_mediaMetricsTimer.isActive())
2744 m_mediaMetricsTimer.stop();
2745 m_mediaMetrics.clear();
2746 return;
2747 }
2748
2749 for (auto* mediaElement : HTMLMediaElement::allMediaElements()) {
2750 if (!is<HTMLVideoElement>(mediaElement) || !mediaElement->isPlaying())
2751 continue;
2752
2753 auto videoPlaybackQuality = mediaElement->getVideoPlaybackQuality();
2754 unsigned displayCompositedVideoFrames = videoPlaybackQuality->displayCompositedVideoFrames();
2755
2756 auto iterator = m_mediaMetrics.find(*mediaElement);
2757 if (iterator == m_mediaMetrics.end()) {
2758 m_mediaMetrics.set(*mediaElement, MediaMetrics(displayCompositedVideoFrames));
2759 continue;
2760 }
2761
2762 bool isPowerEfficient = (displayCompositedVideoFrames - iterator->value.displayCompositedFrames) > 0;
2763 if (iterator->value.isPowerEfficient != isPowerEfficient) {
2764 iterator->value.isPowerEfficient = isPowerEfficient;
2765
2766 if (auto nodeId = pushNodePathToFrontend(mediaElement)) {
2767 auto timestamp = m_environment.executionStopwatch().elapsedTime().seconds();
2768 m_frontendDispatcher->powerEfficientPlaybackStateChanged(nodeId, timestamp, iterator->value.isPowerEfficient);
2769 }
2770 }
2771
2772 iterator->value.displayCompositedFrames = displayCompositedVideoFrames;
2773 }
2774
2775 m_mediaMetrics.removeIf([&] (auto& entry) {
2776 return !HTMLMediaElement::allMediaElements().contains(&entry.key);
2777 });
2778}
2779#endif
2780
2781Node* InspectorDOMAgent::nodeForPath(const String& path)
2782{
2783 // The path is of form "1,HTML,2,BODY,1,DIV"
2784 if (!m_document)
2785 return nullptr;
2786
2787 Node* node = m_document.get();
2788 Vector<String> pathTokens = path.split(',');
2789 if (!pathTokens.size())
2790 return nullptr;
2791
2792 for (size_t i = 0; i < pathTokens.size() - 1; i += 2) {
2793 auto childNumber = parseIntegerAllowingTrailingJunk<unsigned>(pathTokens[i]);
2794 if (!childNumber)
2795 return nullptr;
2796
2797 Node* child;
2798 if (is<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(*node)) {
2799 ASSERT(!*childNumber);
2800 auto& frameOwner = downcast<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(*node);
2801 child = frameOwner.contentDocument();
2802 } else {
2803 if (*childNumber >= innerChildNodeCount(node))
2804 return nullptr;
2805 child = innerFirstChild(node);
2806 for (size_t j = 0; child && j < *childNumber; ++j)
2807 child = innerNextSibling(child);
2808 }
2809
2810 const auto& childName = pathTokens[i + 1];
2811 if (!child || child->nodeName() != childName)
2812 return nullptr;
2813 node = child;
2814 }
2815 return node;
2816}

2818Node* InspectorDOMAgent::nodeForObjectId(const Protocol::Runtime::RemoteObjectId& objectId)
2819{
2820 InjectedScript injectedScript = m_injectedScriptManager.injectedScriptForObjectId(objectId);
2821 if (injectedScript.hasNoValue())
2822 return nullptr;
2823
2824 return scriptValueAsNode(injectedScript.findObjectById(objectId));
2825}

2827Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Protocol::DOM::NodeId> InspectorDOMAgent::pushNodeByPathToFrontend(const String& path)
2828{
2829 Protocol::ErrorString errorString;
2830
2831 if (Node* node = nodeForPath(path)) {
2832 if (auto nodeId = pushNodePathToFrontend(errorString, node))
2833 return nodeId;
2834 return makeUnexpected(errorString);
2835 }
2836
2837 return makeUnexpected("Missing node for given path"_s);
2838}

2840RefPtr<Protocol::Runtime::RemoteObject> InspectorDOMAgent::resolveNode(Node* node, const String& objectGroup)
2841{
2842 Document* document = &node->document();
2843 if (auto* templateHost = document->templateDocumentHost())
2844 document = templateHost;
2845 auto* frame = document->frame();
2846 if (!frame)
2847 return nullptr;
2848
2849 auto& state = *mainWorldExecState(frame);
2850 auto injectedScript = m_injectedScriptManager.injectedScriptFor(&state);
2851 if (injectedScript.hasNoValue())
2852 return nullptr;
2853
2854 return injectedScript.wrapObject(nodeAsScriptValue(state, node), objectGroup);
2855}

2860 return nullptr;

2862}
